                           ((\"Four\" :keys 4)
                            (\"Five\" :keys 5)
                            (\"Six\"  :keys 6)))))))

returns:

  ((\"1\" \"One\"   entry (file \"\") nil)
   (\"2\" \"Two\"   entry (file \"\") nil)
   (\"3\" \"Three\" entry (file \"\") nil))

Normally template \"Four\" would throw an error because its :keys are not a string."

